### Doctor Authentication API Tests

### 1. Register a new doctor (RegisterDoctorDto)
POST {{host}}/api/doctor-auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Dr. Sarah",
  "middleName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "password": "SecurePassword123",
  "phoneNumber": "0912345678",
  "gender": 2,
  "dateOfBirth": "1985-03-20T00:00:00Z"
}

### 2. Verify OTP (VerifyDoctorOtpDto - use the OTP returned from registration)
POST {{host}}/api/doctor-auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0912345678",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### 3. Login with phone number and password (LoginDoctorDto)
POST {{host}}/api/doctor-auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0912345678",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

### 4. Forgot password (ForgotDoctorPasswordDto - send OTP for password reset)
POST {{host}}/api/doctor-auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0912345678"
}

### 5. Reset password (ResetDoctorPasswordDto - use the OTP returned from forgot password)
POST {{host}}/api/doctor-auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0912345678",
  "otp": "123456",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePassword456"
}

### 6. Get my profile (requires authentication - add Bearer token to Authorization header)
GET {{host}}/api/doctor-auth/my-profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

